President Obama spoke with UK Prime Minister David Cameron about the crises in Iraq and Ukraine, as well as the Ebola outbreak in West Africa. They agreed to provide additional humanitarian assistance for Iraq and develop options to ensure the safety of civilians on Mount Sinjar. They also discussed countering the threat of ISIL in Iraq and emphasized the need for an inclusive government. Regarding Ukraine, they condemned any Russian intervention without the consent of the Ukrainian government, calling it a violation of international law. They also called for an immediate cessation of hostilities in Gaza and expressed support for Israel's right to self-defense while urging all sides to minimize civilian casualties. Lastly, they welcomed the efforts of the World Health Organization in addressing the Ebola outbreak and pledged increased assistance from the US and UK governments.